== Sweet Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{}
with a large drizzle of @oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until
browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Sweet Potato Wedges ==

While sweet potatoes roast, halve @Roma tomato{1} lengthwise; thinly slice
crosswise into half-moons. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Drain
@corn{13.4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @ranch dressing{1.5%ounce} and
@smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @tempura mix{82%g}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon},
and @cold water{1/3%cup} until smooth. Stir in corn, half the cilantro,
@pepper{}, and @salt{3/4%tsp}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2/3 cup cold water and 1 1/2 tsp salt.

> TIP: If mixture is too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches
> a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large heavy-bottomed pan{}
over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when
added to the pan, add heaping ¼-cup scoops of batter to pan, making 6-8 fritters.

Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer fritters to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Season
with a pinch of @salt{}.

> 4 SERVINGS: You'll make 12-16 fritters.

> TIP: You may need to cook fritters in batches. Lower heat if fritters are browning
> too quickly.

== Side Salad ==

In a second #large bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce} and tomato with as much
smoky ranch dressing as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide corn fritters, sweet potatoes, and salad between plates. Sprinkle fritters
with remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining smoky ranch dressing on the side.